# prometheus.service — Host-first deployment systemd unit

## Overview

This systemd unit file runs Prometheus for the LLM proxy stack monitoring
infrastructure. It uses the host-first model (binary installation, no
containers) and is designed to be deployed as a **user service**.

## User Service (Recommended)

**File location**: `~/.config/systemd/user/prometheus.service`

```ini
[Unit]
Description=Prometheus metrics server for LLM proxy stack
After=network.target llama-proxy.service
Wants=network.target

[Service]
Type=simple
ExecStart=/home/rgardler/bin/prometheus/prometheus \
  --config.file=/home/rgardler/projects/llm/monitoring/prometheus.yml \
  --storage.tsdb.path=/home/rgardler/.local/share/prometheus/data \
  --storage.tsdb.retention.time=15d \
  --web.listen-address=:9090

# Restart policy
Restart=always
RestartSec=5

# Logging
StandardOutput=append:/home/rgardler/.local/state/prometheus/logs/prometheus.log
StandardError=append:/home/rgardler/.local/state/prometheus/logs/prometheus.log

# Resource limits
MemoryMax=4G

[Install]
WantedBy=default.target
```

### Setup commands (user service)

```bash
# Create directories
mkdir -p ~/.local/share/prometheus/data
mkdir -p ~/.local/state/prometheus/logs

# Enable and start the service
systemctl --user daemon-reload
systemctl --user enable prometheus.service
systemctl --user start prometheus.service

# Check status
systemctl --user status prometheus.service

# View logs
journalctl --user -u prometheus.service -f
```

## Verification

```bash
# Check Prometheus targets page
curl http://localhost:9090/api/v1/targets

# Check metrics endpoint
curl http://localhost:9090/api/v1/query?query=up

# View Prometheus expression browser
# Open http://localhost:9090 in a browser

# Query a specific metric
curl 'http://localhost:9090/api/v1/query?query=llama_process_rss_bytes'
```

